Mauritius Stocks Snap 2-Day Drop, Led by Mauritius Hotels

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-05-06T11:02:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/mauritius-stocks-snap-two-day-drop-led-by-nmh-sun-as-tourists-increase.html
Mauritius’s stocks gauge rose the most
in two weeks, led by  New Mauritius Hotels Ltd. (NMH) , after l’Express
reported tourism arrivals climbed 10 percent in April from a
year earlier.  The 37-member gauge snapped two days of losses, rallying
0.5 percent to 2,061.14 by the 1:30 p.m. close in the capital,
 Port Louis , the biggest gain since April 22.  New Mauritius Hotels, the Indian Ocean island nation’s
biggest leisure group by market value, added 3 percent to 103
rupees, the strongest advance since Feb. 11. Sun Resorts Ltd.,
the second-largest, surged 1.6 percent to 63 rupees, an 11-month
high.  Mauritius attracted 64,797 tourists in April, the Port
Louis-based newspaper cited Mauritius Tourism Promotion
Authority Director Karl Mootoosamy as saying. Tourism accounts
for the bulk of the nation’s foreign-currency earnings, with
 Europe  accounting for 67 percent of tourists, the agency said
April 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
